cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a neural model for clustering data points drawn from low-dimensional subspaces. This involves the use of a classifier and the construction of affinity matrices for training. Given the focus on neural models and machine learning techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of affinity matrices and subspace-based clustering also suggests potential relevance to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as self-expressiveness, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of a collaborative scheme for training suggests potential relevance to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
